18/02/2005
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- OSCE High Commissioner on National Minorities Rolf Ekeus visited Belgrade on Thursday (17 February) to discuss ethnic relations.
He met with Serbian Prime Minister Vojislav Kostunica, Human Rights Minister Rasim Ljajic and Kosovo Co-ordination Centre head Nebojsa Covic.
Ekeus called for an integrative approach to ethnic minorities, rejecting secession as an option.
He also acknowledged the OSCE should work harder to ensure problems in Kosovo are resolved.
In other news, Serbian authorities have arrested six war crimes suspects in connection with the first case transferred from the UN tribunal to the local judiciary.
Prosecutors investigated nine suspects in all and are still looking for three of them.
No names have been released.
(B92, Reuters, Beta - 17/02/05)
